<PageLayout title="Disclosure" description="Advertising, affiliate, and editorial disclosure for FlowHat Blog">
	<h1>Disclosure</h1>
	<p>
		FlowHat Blog is an independent publication focused on LLMs, AI agents, coding tools, and practical
		workflows. The site may earn revenue through display advertising, affiliate links, sponsorships, or
		other commercial relationships. This page explains how those relationships are handled.
	</p>

	<h2>Advertising</h2>
	<p>
		FlowHat Blog may display ads through Google AdSense or other advertising networks. Advertising
		partners may use cookies, scripts, or similar technologies to serve ads, measure ad performance, and
		protect against invalid activity.
	</p>
	<p>
		Ads do not determine which topics are covered or what conclusions are published. Editorial content
		is selected based on relevance to LLMs, agents, coding tools, software workflows, and practical value
		for readers.
	</p>

	<h2>Affiliate links</h2>
	<p>
		Some outbound links may be affiliate links. If a visitor clicks an affiliate link and makes a
		qualifying purchase, FlowHat Blog may earn a commission at no additional cost to the visitor.
	</p>
	<p>
		Affiliate relationships do not guarantee positive coverage. A product, tool, or service may be
		mentioned because it is useful, relevant, widely used, technically interesting, or important to the
		agent-tooling ecosystem. When a link is commercial in nature, the site aims to keep that relationship
		clear to readers.
	</p>

	<h2>Product mentions and tool coverage</h2>
	<p>
		FlowHat Blog often writes about products, models, repositories, and developer tools from companies
		such as OpenAI, Anthropic, Google, Meta, xAI, Hugging Face, Moonshot AI, Qwen, and independent open
		source projects. Mentioning a product or company does not mean the article is sponsored or endorsed
		by that company.
	</p>
	<p>
		Unless clearly stated otherwise, posts are editorial content and not paid placements.
	</p>

	<h2>Sponsored content</h2>
	<p>
		If FlowHat Blog publishes sponsored content in the future, it will be identified as sponsored,
		promotional, or paid content. Sponsored content should not be presented as independent editorial
		coverage.
	</p>

	<h2>Corrections and updates</h2>
	<p>
		AI tooling changes quickly. Posts may be updated when products change, links break, or important
		context becomes available. Updates are intended to improve accuracy and usefulness, not to hide
		commercial relationships.
	</p>

	<p><strong>Last updated:</strong> May 4, 2026</p>
</PageLayout>
